%F A390597 For p an odd prime, a(p) = min{m : ord_p(m^(p - 1) - 1) = p}.
%F A390597 For n >= 2, a(n) <= n^n - 1.
%e A390597 a(4) = 26 since 26 = 122_4 is the smallest integer (greater than 1) whose constant congruence speed exists and equals 4.
